Information for Jool:

Heights for Jool

-flight 2793m - 107700m

-upper atmosphere None! or that I could find

-space near Jool (107700 - 4000 km)

-space high above Jool (4000 km - SOI limit)

Obligatory "Oh my God it's full of stars quote"

-upper atmosphere None! or that I could find

I've noticed that upper atmosphere is fidgity on all planets. On kerbin, for example, I've found upper atmosphere as high as 68 km, but near space as low as 32 km.

I've never missed upper atmosphere on Jool, but you need to come in almost circularly, otherwise you're "flying" before you know it. I've hit upper atmosphere on Jool as high as 135 km, but only when I came in very slowly and gently and aerobraked into an almost circular orbit at that height.
All these biomes should show up on the "info" tab in Map view when you find them, so you can keep track of which areas are left to explore.

Skipping through the thread I didn't find anyone else commenting on this, so I'll throw my own observations in:

Slowly spiraling in to Duna, I was forced into physical time warp at ~41,500m, however my instrumentation (thermometer, barometer) would not function until I got down around 31,000 or so. My persistence file has the following log in it:

		Science
		{
			id = temperatureScan@DunaFlyingHigh
			title = Temperature Scan from Duna's upper atmosphere
			dsc = 1
			scv = 0.01977059
			sbv = 5
			sci = 49.01147
			cap = 50
		}

I don't know what all those variables mean but unfortunately there's no apparent altitude included But at least "Upper Atmosphere" starts somewhere between 41,500 and ~30,000 meters!
